"metaSummary_en": "With the arrival of Everyday Wonders (B3b), the meta has completely reshuffled: Miraidon ex Magnezone takes the lead (7.87% usage, 51.85% win rate) ahead of the brand-new Greninja Mega Sableye ex (7.26%, 52.38%), while the heavily played Mega Gardevoir ex Mega Diancie ex (6.35%) disappoints at just 43.65% win rate. The best genuinely playable win rate belongs to the Mega Sceptile variants: Mega Sceptile ex Greninja tops out at 63.06% (2.57% usage) and Butterfree Mega Sceptile ex at 61.97%, ahead of Suicune ex Baxcalibur (57.45%) and Zoroark ex Mega Absol ex (56.00%). The old kings of the B3a format have fallen sharply — Mega Altaria ex Espeon drops from 1st place to about 1.4% usage — replaced by the new Everyday Wonders decks (Greninja/Mega Sableye, Mega Diancie, Milotic, Butterfree, Hisuian Zoroark). The sample is still modest (661 players across 10 tournaments) and the next major expansion, Ruler of the Skies (B4, July 30, Mega Rayquaza ex), will reshuffle the deck again.",
